Package froggerGame.models.actors

Class MovingActor

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.image.ImageView
froggerGame.models.actors.Actor
froggerGame.models.actors.MovingActor
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
Direct Known Subclasses:
DryTurtle, Log, Obstacle, Player, WetTurtle
public abstract class MovingActor
extends Actor

MovingActor

The MovingActor is an abstract class expanding on Actor. Objects of this type can move from point A to point B. The MovingActor class is the superclass of many mobs in the game. It also implements respawning and despawning of mobs with leftDespawnPos, rightDespawnPos, leftRespawnPos, rightRespawnPos with left indicating that it travels from left to right, and from right to left for right.

Author:
hfyns3
See Also:
Log, Car, Truck

      public void despawnAndRespawnAnimActor()
      Despawns an actor when it is out of bounds and respawns it. Since mobs only move horizontally, it does not care about the y-coordinate and only bothers with the x-coordinate.
